snippet.textDisplay:
I think the volvo did a great job,
First is has an 4cylilnder, so yeah.... but still pretty fast, and who uses launch control at the head light? No one, on a normal day.

Then its weight, it weights more then the other cars.

After 120kmp the electromotor isn't helping anymore so its then a 305 horsepower engine, and seeing its weight it went pretty dang well.

Then its price... in the Netherlands it is like 67000, and the other cars are over a 110k. So yeah thats with no options and the Volvo is full option. If you put some option on them as you did with the Volvo you come around 130-140k for the Germans...... You can do allot of nice stuff with 60k... you could buy a sporty hatchback and tune the hack out of it. Seeing the Volvo with its comfort and all of his options plus the things i just said it is for me the clear winner. Having a really fast car at the headlights, and being really comfy is just amazing. And you could even have a nice car next to the Volvo wich you could tune so heavy.

For me the polestar one is the sporty Volvo. This s60 is a great daily driver, wich doesn't consume as much as the other three cars. I could drive to work on the electricmotors so yeah.

I have spoken.
